<paragraph pageNumber="863">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="863">Note:</emphasis>
Gray (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="863">Proc. Amer. Acad. Arts</emphasis>
17: 178. 1882) discussed the identity of various of the original elements, noting that 998.14 (LINN) is identifiable as 
<taxonomicName authority="L." authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Solidago" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caesia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="863">S. caesia</emphasis>
L.
</taxonomicName>
, but did not designate a type. Other authors such as Mackenzie (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="863">Rhodora</emphasis>
30: 223. 1928) and Taylor &amp; Taylor (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="863">Sida</emphasis>
10: 181. 1983) also discussed this material, but the earliest formal type choice appears to be that of Semple.
</paragraph>
